   To stay within both(subjects) ,  it makes me really mad that the signs in New York are in both English and Spanish.   Most jobs ask for bilinguals , english/spanish.  This is an english speaking country last time I heard.   When I came to the US I learned to speak english as did many other people from other countries.  Now why is it so hard for the spanish speaking to learn how to speak english?  I remember asking this one spanish speaking person why she didn't speak english, and her response was that if I wanted to understand her I should speak spanish.   This country, especially the state of New York is full of people from different countries, why should the spanish speaking have preferential treatment , why not have signs in french, polish, greek.....etc?  To top it all off, some signs are only in spanish. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=26><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#200985><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=confound>CoNfOuNd</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://peter.armo.co.uk/img/irish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Createur de Projets<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-admin.gif' /><br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-vip.gif' /></span><br>  Posts: <b>1712</b><br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#99CCFF>Posted: 10/15/02 7:19:12 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: -</span><hr size=1> Heh, because New York is Spain silly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://w